Hi, Mike! I'm a resident in a hospital based in Beijing. I'm glad you have come up to fight the misinformation and show your support!
1. I believe all Chinese medical staff are trying whatever we can to help patients and fight the virus, while some other specialists are also running clinical trials on new anti-viral medicine on the front lines. Govt has done pretty much everything to restrict the spreading and make info. transparent as possible, such as sharing the virus sequence. Almost every individual now is staying at home and cooperating properly.
2. I've seen much stigma going on. Here I want to tell the people. I understand it's difficult for anyone who doesn't know much about China to be able to differentiate between the government and the people. But I'm sure at this moment we need trust and tolerance than any time.

snippet.textDisplay: I’d like to post a quote from someone I follow about the argument that the flu kills more people than coronavirus. “When people point out that more people die from seasonal flu each year than how many have been killed by Wuhan coronavirus so far, they seem to forget that the flu infects vastly more people. According to the CDC, there were about 38,000 deaths due to flu during the 2016-2017 season, but that was out of over 29 million infections. That means the death rate for seasonal flu was 0.13%. The coronavirus, on the other hand, has killed more than 800 people so far (that we know of) out of 37,000 infections (as of 2/8/2020). That’s about 2.16%, or about seventeen times higher. And let’s not forget, those who die from the infection before diagnosis aren’t included in official figures, and it’s safe to assume the Chinese government is concealing the true death toll (since they arrest people for posting videos about it on social media), which is likely much higher.” - Dr Shaym. Just found this interesting and I believe that the coronavirus may well be more serious than people let on.

And let’s not forget, those who die from the infection before diagnosis aren’t included in official figures, and it’s safe to assume the Chinese government is concealing the true death toll (since they arrest people for posting videos about it on social media), which is likely much higher.” - Dr Shaym. Just found this interesting and I believe that the coronavirus may well be more serious than people let on.
